{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed to complete automatically for `commons-httpclient:commons-httpclient:3.0`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2304-library-new-request-commons-httpclient-commons-httpclient-3.0-89436e91\n\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation review, not final compilation. The generated run took 132 iterations and produced 4,994 LOC, but dynamic-access coverage only reached 24/67 (35.82%). The preserved diff also drifted out of scope for a `library-new-request`: it edits shared TCK support in `tests/tck-test-support/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/NativeImageSupport.java` and `tests/tck-test-support/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/NativeImageSupportTest.java`, and many generated tests are class-loading probes such as `tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/HttpClientTest.java`, `CookiePolicyTest.java`, and `StringPartTest.java` rather than a tight library-specific test set.\n\nThe logs show the generation loop was unstable before those shared-support changes. `human-intervention-logs/commons-httpclient:commons-httpclient:3.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-13T18-09-48-034719Z.log` failed because `native-image-agent` was missing, `human-intervention-logs/commons-httpclient:commons-httpclient:3.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-13T18-09-50-474756Z.log` reported `TraceMetadataConditionPackages` set to `commons-httpclient`, and `human-intervention-logs/commons-httpclient:commons-httpclient:3.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-13T18-24-01-604266Z.log` plus `human-intervention-logs/commons-httpclient:commons-httpclient:3.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-13T18-32-53-924022Z.log` show native-test failures from `ClassNotFoundException`